&lt;p&gt;ADVERT FOR BAND 7 PRACTICE DEVELOPMENT NURSE - NEONATES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kettering General Hospital NHS Foundation Trust – Local Neonatal Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 7 Practice Development Nurse – Neonates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Neonatal Unit is looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic individual to join our friendly and well established Neonatal team as a Band 7 Practice Development Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The individual will work collaboratively with the other Neonatal Practice Development Nurse to support the ongoing development of KGH Children’s Service as a whole and provide a supportive, responsive approach to training and the development of the neonatal nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a skilled and experienced practitioner with a strong clinical and leadership background, the post holder will support practice to drive change and embed a culture of continuous learning and improvement for all of the staff within the clinical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are dedicated to contributing to a team striving to deliver excellence in neonatal care and serious about pursuing a rewarding career in neonatal nursing, then Kettering General Hospital is the place for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHO ARE WE?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Level 2 Local Neonatal Unit with 18 cots incorporating 4 Intensive care, 6 high dependency and 8 special care cots. The Unit is part of the East Midlands Newborn Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Caroline Nyawira&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Neonatal Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address caroline.nyawira1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536492883&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
